Class QualityAnalysis

  • java.lang.Object
    • analysis.QualityAnalysis

  • public class QualityAnalysis
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains the logic of analyzing the quality of sequences (poin) Thus, it is one of the main parts of the analyzing pipeline.

      • checkIfSequenceIsClean

        public static void checkIfSequenceIsClean(AnalysedSequence toAnalyse)
                                   throws CorruptedSequenceException
        This method is called before analysing a sequence but after the trimming them. It checks if any 'X' are in the trimmed sequence. This would mean the sequence is corrupt and cant be analysed.
        Parameters:
        toAnalyse - the sequence to check if there is any corrupt nucleotide.
        Throws:
        CorruptedSequenceException - if there is any corruption then throw this exception.
        See Also:
        MutationAnalysis

      • findLowQuality

        public static int[] findLowQuality(AnalysedSequence sequence)
        This method checks the nucleotide string and finds a position to trim the low quality part at the end of the sequence.
        Parameters:
        sequence - the sequence getting from the abi file
        Returns:
        an Integer, that gives you the position at the end of the sequence to trim the low quality part.
